description: Ramona Optics has created the world's first gigapixel microscopes that can capture extremely high resolution images and videos across large areas. It's core technology, the multi-camera array microscope (MCAM), uses an array of camera sensors and lenses and advanced post-processing software to unlock new possibilities within biomedical research and high-throughput discovery. Please check out some of our videos that both describe our new technology and showcase some of the novel measurements and readouts that it can provide. Learn more at ramonaoptics.com!

description: Welcome to the Dweller Studios Youtube Channel.  In my videos there will be some terrible painting and all kinds of ridiculous things.  I have been painting miniatures almost a year now.  I paint both historical and fantasy and do not use the miniatures for gaming....yet.  If you are looking to learn something or gain valuable knowledge, this is not the place haha.  I might accidently teach something but doubtful.  The channel is just going to be for fun and messing around.  I don't take myself to seriously as you will see.  Hope you will subscribe and watch and enjoy.  Thanks for the visit.

Kevin Lutolf (born December 28, 1996) is a Swiss model, entrepreneur, content creator, actor, fitness influencer, and social media personality. He is the co-founder and CEO of Kompleazy, a video production company. Kevin Lutolf also provides fitness training through his website, where he shares workout regimes and plans.
Kevin Lutolf is known to have garnered international recognition for his modeling work and fitness content. With over a million followers on his multiple social media handles, he continues to inspire and entertain his fans with his creative and captivating content.
Kevin Lutolf was born on December 28, 1996, in, Switzerland. In 2000, he began his apprenticeship at the Vocational School Lenzburg, where he learned about 3D and 5D tool making in plastics, materials, and electrical engineering. He also holds a degree in business administration and applied technical management from Anavant Basel Technical Cadre, which he obtained in 2014.

Welcome to the Rythmagica YouTube Channel!

Here, we're all about the excitement and rhythm of Taiko no Tatsujin, the ultimate rhythm game! Our star product, the TDC10, is a pro drum controller developed by Rythmagica. In April 2024, we successfully completed our first round of Kickstarter crowdfunding. Thanks to timely communication, efficient service, and transparent handling, our backers were thrilled with the process, and we delivered on our promises.

We're proud to say that TDC10 has been embraced by users in over 15 countries. Every TDC10 unit is working flawlessly, bringing more Taiko fun to everyone.

On this channel, you'll find all kinds of videos related to TDC10. We'll introduce you to its features, show you tips and tricks, and share user experiences. Whether you're a seasoned player or new to Taiko no Tatsujin, there's something here for you.

Subscribe now and join our community as we explore the world of rhythm gaming together!

description:
I share my passion for clay with a mixture of demonstration, tutorial and showcase videos from my studio, Paula Armstrong Ceramics. Full of how to videos, hints and tips for hand building in clay as well as insights into the making process for my sculptures and the running of the studio, this channel has something for anyone who loves clay but especially for those towards the beginning of their clay journey.

I love making with clay and helping people to learn to make with clay.  I love the versatility and endless possibilities of clay as a medium and sharing that with you in the hopes of inspiring and helping you on your own making journey.

I aim to upload a new video every couple of weeks so if you have any video ideas or different topics you'd like to see covered please do let me know!
